# Accepted OS-level CVEs with no fix in Debian Bookworm.
# Mitigated by container hardening: cap-drop ALL, read-only rootfs,
# no-new-privileges, rootless mode.
# Reassess on base image upgrade to Debian Trixie or Node 24.

# zlib: integer overflow in zipOpenNewFileInZip4_64 (minizip); will_not_fix by Debian
CVE-2023-45853

# openldap: null pointer dereference in ber_memalloc_x; transitive dep via libcurl
CVE-2023-2953

# git: arbitrary code execution via crafted repository
CVE-2025-48384

# git: arbitrary file writes via crafted repository
CVE-2025-48385

# glibc: integer overflow in memalign
CVE-2026-0861

# sqlite: integer overflow in SQLite; no fixed Bookworm package yet
CVE-2025-7458

# npm transitive deps — npm 11.11.0 vendors glob 10.4.5,
# minimatch 10.2.2 / 9.0.5, and tar 6.2.1 / 7.4.3.
# Fixes require glob >= 10.5.0, minimatch >= 10.2.3 / 9.0.7,
# and tar >= 7.5.8, but npm bundles private @npmcli packages
# that cannot be patched independently.
# Mitigated: read-only rootfs, cap-drop ALL, no-new-privileges.
# Reassess on the next npm release that updates these vendored deps.

# glob: command injection via malicious pattern (fixed in 10.5.0 / 11.1.0)
CVE-2025-64756

# minimatch: DoS via unbounded backtracking (fixed in 10.2.3 / 9.0.7)
CVE-2026-27903

# minimatch: DoS via catastrophic backtracking (fixed in 10.2.3 / 9.0.7)
CVE-2026-27904

# minimatch: DoS via specially crafted pattern (fixed in 9.0.6)
CVE-2026-26996

# tar: arbitrary file overwrite and symlink attack (fixed in 7.5.3)
CVE-2026-23745

# tar: arbitrary file overwrite via crafted archive (fixed in 7.5.4)
CVE-2026-23950

# tar: arbitrary file creation via path traversal (fixed in 7.5.7)
CVE-2026-24842

# tar: arbitrary file read/write via symlink (fixed in 7.5.8)
CVE-2026-26960

# tar: hardlink path traversal via drive-relative linkpath (fixed in 7.5.10)
CVE-2026-29786

# libexpat: integer overflow causing info disclosure / data integrity issues
CVE-2026-25210

# openssh: GSSAPI uninitialized memory — info disclosure or DoS
CVE-2026-3497

# tar: file overwrite via drive-relative symlink traversal (fixed in 7.5.11)
CVE-2026-31802

# gh CLI gobinary — docker/cli transitive dep
# Mitigated: Linux-only sandbox, no Docker socket access.
# Reassess on next gh release that updates docker/cli.

# docker/cli: Windows privilege escalation (fixed in 29.2.0)
CVE-2025-15558

# systemd/libudev1: arbitrary code execution or DoS via spurious IPC
CVE-2026-29111

# ncurses: buffer overflow may lead to arbitrary code execution
CVE-2025-69720

# openssh-client: privilege escalation via scp legacy protocol
CVE-2026-35385

# picomatch: ReDoS via crafted extglob patterns (fixed in 4.0.4)
CVE-2026-33671

# nghttp2: DoS via malformed HTTP/2; no fix in Debian Bookworm yet
CVE-2026-27135
